HB 1096 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Jacob Landry
Abstract: Provides relative to the adopting, amending, or repealing of bylaws of an electric
cooperative.
Present law provides relative to the bylaws of electric cooperatives.
Present law provides that bylaws may be adopted, amended, or repealed by the members,
or by the board of directors.
Proposed law amends present law to provide that, unless otherwise provided in the bylaws,
bylaws may be adopted, amended, or repealed by the board of directors.
(Amends R.S. 12:407(B))
